CNCP v1 23692
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7433: Allow generics for Data, Methods, Computed and Props in defineComponent to ease migration from Vue2",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:13.951479+00:00",
  "text": "Allow generics for Data, Methods, Computed and Props in defineComponent to ease migration from Vue2\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\r\n\r\nWe have a largish code base in Vue2 and are looking into upgrading it to Vue3. We already use Typescript, but without class components. The way we write components in Vue2 is this:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport Vue from 'vue'\r\n\r\ninterface Data {\r\n  isActive: boolean\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface Methods {\r\n  updateRemote(payload: ApiPayload, options: ApiOptions): void\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface Computed {\r\n  selectItems: <string, number>[]\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface Props {\r\n  mapType: \"osm\" | \"swiss\" | \"france\"\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport default Vue.extend<Data, Methods, Computed, Props>({\r\n  name: 'MyComponent',\r\n  props: [\"mapType\"], // or object\r\n  data() {\r\n     isActive: false\r\n  },\r\n  methods: {\r\n    updateRemote(payload, options) {}\r\n  },\r\n  computed: {\r\n    selectItems() { }\r\n  }\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis has worked well for us so far. In Vue3, `extend` [has been removed](https://v3-migration.vuejs.org/breaking-changes/global-api.html#type-inference) and the way to go is to use `defineComponent`. However, this function doesn't seem to expose the same generics as `Vue.extend` did. This makes migration from Vue2 quite costly.\r\n\r\nDo you see a way to retrofit `defineComponent` with an overload that accepts Data, Methods, Computed and Props as Typescript generics?\r\n\r\nPartly related to https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/3102\r\n\r\n### What does the proposed API look like?\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst myComponent = defineComponent<Data, Methods, Computed, Props>({\r\n  ...\r\n})\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: types"
  ],
